Yep.

496
00:44:46,057 --> 00:44:47,849
- I'll see you there as well.
- Yes, sir.

497
00:44:48,018 --> 00:44:49,518
Thank you.

498
00:44:51,313 --> 00:44:53,063
So I heard you raised enough money...

499
00:44:53,231 --> 00:44:56,275
...to give a couple of the kids
partial scholarships to college.

500
00:44:56,443 --> 00:44:58,402
It's no big deal.

501
00:44:58,570 --> 00:45:00,737
I just convinced a couple
of bigwig donors...

502
00:45:00,905 --> 00:45:04,701
...that what the world really needs
to see is more Latinos on ice.

503
00:45:08,831 --> 00:45:12,208
You know, Ben, I keep asking you this...

504
00:45:12,376 --> 00:45:15,545
...but why me?

505
00:45:17,338 --> 00:45:21,259
Because you are a good man.

506
00:45:21,427 --> 00:45:24,052
No, really.

507
00:45:25,264 --> 00:45:29,726
Even when you don't know
that people are watching you.

508
00:45:41,572 --> 00:45:48,577
Hello?

509
00:45:52,081 --> 00:45:55,083
<i>Okay, I can't hear you, so try back again.</i>

510
00:45:56,085 --> 00:45:58,086
Gonna hang up now.

511
00:45:58,963 --> 00:46:00,757
Bye.

512
00:46:12,811 --> 00:46:14,603
Mr. Thomas?

513
00:46:14,771 --> 00:46:16,731
We're ready for you.

514
00:47:44,485 --> 00:47:47,070
These are beautiful.

515
00:47:47,239 --> 00:47:50,199
Banana peels. Who knew?

516
00:48:17,226 --> 00:48:18,811
Emily?

517
00:49:54,992 --> 00:49:56,951
Can I get a refill?

518
00:49:59,996 --> 00:50:02,331
- Susan?
- Yeah.

519
00:50:02,498 --> 00:50:03,666
How's Ryan?

520
00:50:04,083 --> 00:50:07,085
He's good. He's at his dad's this weekend.

521
00:50:07,253 --> 00:50:13,717
Will you tell him for me that I'm ready
whenever he is for a free lesson?

522
00:50:13,885 --> 00:50:15,010
Yeah, all right.

523
00:50:15,177 --> 00:50:17,512
Things are kind of crazy
right now with school...

524
00:50:17,681 --> 00:50:19,514
...but maybe when school's out.

525
00:50:19,682 --> 00:50:22,351
Oh, yeah. That's perfect.

526
00:50:47,960 --> 00:50:50,045
How's the pie?

527
00:50:50,213 --> 00:50:53,090
Oh, it's... it's good.

528
00:50:53,257 --> 00:50:55,342
You gonna ask her out?

529
00:50:56,510 --> 00:50:57,969
The waitress.

530
00:51:01,516 --> 00:51:02,974
No.

531
00:51:03,518 --> 00:51:04,893
You never know.

532
00:51:07,021 --> 00:51:10,565
I don't... I don't think she sees me.

533
00:51:12,902 --> 00:51:14,402
Good night, Ezra.

534
00:51:52,650 --> 00:51:53,983
Hello?

535
00:51:55,862 --> 00:51:57,445
Ben?

536
00:51:58,405 --> 00:52:00,449
Hi, I'm sorry to call so late.

537
00:52:03,577 --> 00:52:07,206
Did...? Did someone
from the IRS contact you?

538
00:52:07,373 --> 00:52:09,208
No.

539
00:52:09,376 --> 00:52:11,043
I just...

540
00:52:12,003 --> 00:52:16,297
I was having trouble breathing after
I took Duke for a walk, and I fainted.

541
00:52:17,050 --> 00:52:19,885
<i>An ambulance had to take
me to the hospital.</i>

542
00:52:21,847 --> 00:52:23,054
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

543
00:52:23,222 --> 00:52:25,306
I don't know why I even
called you. I'm sorry.

544
00:52:25,474 --> 00:52:28,978
It's just that I have your card
with me, and...

545
00:52:33,023 --> 00:52:34,233
Ben?

546
00:52:37,445 --> 00:52:39,155
Are you still there?

547
00:52:40,072 --> 00:52:41,614
Yes.

548
00:52:45,161 --> 00:52:47,496
Do you ever think about dying, Ben?

549
00:52:49,748 --> 00:52:51,583
Every now and again.

550
00:52:53,378 --> 00:52:56,380
My face is bluish.

551
00:52:56,547 --> 00:52:59,550
It's not exactly a good sign.

552
00:52:59,717 --> 00:53:02,260
You should try to rest. Just...

553
00:53:02,429 --> 00:53:05,181
Why don't you see
if you can get some sleep?

554
00:53:06,016 --> 00:53:08,266
I like talking to you.

555
00:53:08,434 --> 00:53:10,603
<i>I like talking to you too.</i>

556
00:53:13,815 --> 00:53:16,275
Would you tell me a story, please?

557
00:53:20,530 --> 00:53:22,197
Okay.

558
00:53:25,034 --> 00:53:28,077
All right. Once upon a time...

559
00:53:28,246 --> 00:53:32,248
<i>...there was a little boy named...</i>

560
00:53:32,416 --> 00:53:36,670
Oh, lucky me, you just got it
on reserve like that. Okay.

561
00:53:37,838 --> 00:53:39,965
Let me guess. His name was Ben.

562
00:53:42,219 --> 00:53:46,347
No, actually, this little
boy's name is Tim.

563
00:53:46,514 --> 00:53:48,891
I like the name Tim.

564
00:53:49,059 --> 00:53:50,893
Go on.

565
00:53:51,061 --> 00:53:53,478
<i>Tim's little brother was
always pestering Tim...</i>

566
00:53:53,646 --> 00:53:59,108
...to make him paper airplanes,
because he was really good at it.

567
00:53:59,277 --> 00:54:02,612
But Tim had much bigger dreams than that.

568
00:54:02,780 --> 00:54:05,490
Okay. Then what happened?

569
00:54:06,201 --> 00:54:08,534
One day, Tim went out to the backyard...

570
00:54:08,702 --> 00:54:13,539
...and he put leaves and taped
branches to his arms...

571
00:54:13,708 --> 00:54:15,793
...and started climbing the big oak tree.

572
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:19,713
<i>His little brother said,
"Tim, you can't fly."</i>

573
00:54:19,880 --> 00:54:22,257
<i>And he said, "Yeah? You just watch."</i>

574
00:54:22,425 --> 00:54:26,594
He got all the way to the top and jumped.

575
00:54:28,431 --> 00:54:31,432
How tall was this tree?

576
00:54:31,934 --> 00:54:34,853
<i>It was... it was pretty tall.
He broke his arm.</i>

577
00:54:35,021 --> 00:54:37,690
Oh, my God... This is a horrible story.

578
00:54:37,856 --> 00:54:39,315
Oh, no, no. It gets better.

579
00:54:39,483 --> 00:54:45,155
From that experience,
Tim realized that he wanted to fly.

580
00:54:45,782 --> 00:54:49,451
So he dedicated his life
to making spaceships.

581
00:54:49,619 --> 00:54:52,288
I thought you said this was a good story.

582
00:54:53,664 --> 00:54:55,456
Oh, well...

583
00:54:56,126 --> 00:54:57,876
Yeah, that is...

584
00:54:58,753 --> 00:55:02,130
...until the dragons showed up.

585
00:55:02,715 --> 00:55:06,260
Oh, okay, see, now it's getting better.

586
00:55:06,427 --> 00:55:09,722
I like dragons.
Especially dragons in space.

587
00:55:09,889 --> 00:55:14,476
Yes, and these were
fire-breathing space dragons...

588
00:55:14,643 --> 00:55:17,353
<i>...with really bad attitudes.</i>

589
00:55:18,231 --> 00:55:20,315
I see.

590
00:55:21,818 --> 00:55:23,152
I have an idea.

591
00:55:23,695 --> 00:55:25,695
<i>Why don't you try to fall asleep...</i>

592
00:55:25,864 --> 00:55:29,742
<i>...and when you do, I'll just hang up.</i>

593
00:55:31,786 --> 00:55:33,579
Okay.

594
00:55:35,123 --> 00:55:36,164
Ben?

595
00:55:37,250 --> 00:55:38,708
Yes.

596
00:55:40,503 --> 00:55:43,338
Thank you for listening.

597
00:55:43,505 --> 00:55:45,465
And for talking.

598
00:55:47,552 --> 00:55:49,677
<i>Try to fall asleep.</i>

599
00:55:54,893 --> 00:55:56,684
Good night, Ben.

600
00:55:57,853 --> 00:55:59,688
Good night, Emily.

601
00:56:05,945 --> 00:56:07,045
Emily?

602
00:56:14,800 --> 00:56:16,000
Emily?

603
00:57:09,092 --> 00:57:11,135
I lied to you.

604
00:57:13,471 --> 00:57:16,139
I think about dying every day.

605
00:57:25,442 --> 00:57:30,528
<i>Dr. King to NICU. Dr. Wesley King,
please report to NICU.</i>

606
00:58:12,739 --> 00:58:14,322
Hey.

607
00:58:18,994 --> 00:58:21,496
- Hey.
- Hey.

608
00:58:23,123 --> 00:58:24,583
When did you get here?

609
00:58:27,670 --> 00:58:30,005
Last night, after we talked.

610
00:58:31,590 --> 00:58:33,175
You slept here?

611
00:58:35,302 --> 00:58:37,846
Good morning. How's our patient?

612
00:58:38,014 --> 00:58:40,056
- Morning. Better.
- Good.

613
00:58:40,224 --> 00:58:43,101
- Hello.
- Hi, Ben. Is that right? IRS?

614
00:58:43,268 --> 00:58:45,019
- Yes, how are you?
- Good, thank you.

615
00:58:45,188 --> 00:58:48,231
- I'll leave you two alone.
- No, no, stay, please. Don't go.

616
00:58:48,398 --> 00:58:50,067
He can... He can stay.

617
00:58:50,235 --> 00:58:52,152
Whatever you want.

618
00:58:54,489 --> 00:58:56,572
You fainted because
your heart was too weak...

619
00:58:56,740 --> 00:58:58,534
...to pump enough blood to your brain.

620
00:58:58,701 --> 00:59:01,702
It's enlarged and it's
starting to shut down.

621
00:59:02,496 --> 00:59:03,746
How long?

622
00:59:04,414 --> 00:59:06,458
It's entirely up to your heart.

623
00:59:06,626 --> 00:59:10,545
Could be six weeks, could be a month.

624
00:59:11,213 --> 00:59:13,715
But we've upped you to Status 1 B.

625
00:59:15,677 --> 00:59:17,094
At least I'm on the list.

626
00:59:17,594 --> 00:59:22,099
Not only that, but we're
giving you this pager.

627
00:59:22,266 --> 00:59:26,018
And when it goes off,
it means you have a donor.

628
00:59:29,940 --> 00:59:32,108
The inotrope drug I started you on...

629
00:59:32,277 --> 00:59:35,445
...it's gonna stabilize your
blood pressure within 24 hours.

630
00:59:36,572 --> 00:59:38,072
Then what?

631
00:59:38,240 --> 00:59:40,284
We wait.

632
00:59:40,867 --> 00:59:44,413
- Can I do that at home?
- Once you're stable, you can.

633
00:59:45,039 --> 00:59:46,581
Okay.

634
00:59:58,094 --> 01:00:02,972
I'm gonna run to the cafeteria.
I'm gonna get you something.

635
01:00:03,141 --> 01:00:06,601
If you want something else,
I can get you something else.

636
01:00:10,523 --> 01:00:12,565
Would you stay?

637
01:00:15,445 --> 01:00:18,112
I mean, unless you have
something else to do.

638
01:00:21,117 --> 01:00:25,454
- I'd really like it if you stayed.
- I don't have anything.

639
01:00:27,456 --> 01:00:30,041
Okay. Okay.

640
01:00:46,141 --> 01:00:48,434
Hey, hey, hey. What the hell is that thing?

641
01:00:48,603 --> 01:00:50,646
It's a dog. Just for one night.

642
01:00:50,813 --> 01:00:53,356
No. Hold on, hold on.
I don't give two shits, okay?

643
01:00:53,523 --> 01:00:55,108
We have a dog policy here.

644
01:00:55,275 --> 01:00:57,902
Little dogs only. Poodles and Shih Tzus.

645
01:00:58,070 --> 01:01:01,447
It's in the contract. It's English
and Spanish for everyone to see.

646
01:01:01,615 --> 01:01:04,242
And besides, that, my friend, is not a dog.

647
01:01:04,409 --> 01:01:06,452
It's a goddamn horse.

648
01:01:06,621 --> 01:01:10,498
Well, let me know when you add
a horse policy to the contract.

649
01:01:37,485 --> 01:01:38,527
Yes.

650
01:01:39,237 --> 01:01:41,405
Mr. Thomas, it's Connie Tepos.

651
01:01:42,447 --> 01:01:43,864
Hey, Connie.

652
01:01:44,032 --> 01:01:46,576
<i>I don't know why I'm calling you...</i>

653
01:01:46,744 --> 01:01:49,036
...but I'm calling you.

654
01:01:50,039 --> 01:01:52,039
You said you could help us and...

655
01:01:52,208 --> 01:01:54,583
Can you really help us?

656
01:01:55,378 --> 01:01:57,838
This just doesn't make any sense.

657
01:01:58,380 --> 01:02:00,715
- What if he finds us?
- He won't.

658
01:02:00,882 --> 01:02:02,425
- What makes you so sure?
- Stop it.

659
01:02:02,592 --> 01:02:05,010
- You don't know him.
- Stop it.

660
01:02:05,179 --> 01:02:07,556
Don't be weak.

661
01:02:07,724 --> 01:02:11,393
- Don't be weak.
- I'm not weak.

662
01:02:13,563 --> 01:02:15,896
I'm strong.

663
01:02:17,483 --> 01:02:20,527
Take this. Take it.

664
01:02:22,405 --> 01:02:24,780
You are gonna start this car...

665
01:02:25,867 --> 01:02:27,867
...and you're gonna go.

666
01:02:28,786 --> 01:02:33,081
This is real, and this is
gonna be your new life.

667
01:02:34,083 --> 01:02:36,918
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

668
01:02:37,085 --> 01:02:40,463
Look at those babies.
Look at those babies.

669
01:02:40,630 --> 01:02:42,465
Look how beautiful those babies are.

670
01:02:42,632 --> 01:02:45,010
I know, I know.

671
01:02:46,094 --> 01:02:47,929
They deserve it.

672
01:02:49,891 --> 01:02:51,766
Okay?

673
01:02:53,393 --> 01:02:56,855
<i>You're headed north up the coast.</i>

674
01:03:20,295 --> 01:03:22,338
Lorena. Lorena.

675
01:03:23,548 --> 01:03:27,802
<i>I've always believed
this place can heal the soul.</i>

676
01:03:32,474 --> 01:03:33,974
Mommy, the ocean.

677
01:03:34,143 --> 01:03:35,936
Yes, the ocean.

678
01:03:36,103 --> 01:03:38,646
<i>I hope that proves true for you.</i>

679
01:03:58,416 --> 01:04:02,170
<i>When you sign your name on the
dotted line of the contract...</i>

680
01:04:02,338 --> 01:04:04,922
<i>...you'll own my house outright.</i>

681
01:04:07,885 --> 01:04:10,554
<i>I only ask that you never mention
how you got the house...</i>

682
01:04:10,721 --> 01:04:14,391
<i>...or try to contact me for any reason.</i>

683
01:04:18,728 --> 01:04:22,606
<i>And if you're wondering
why you, please stop.</i>

684
01:04:29,907 --> 01:04:33,117
<i>All I ask is for you to honor my wishes...</i>

685
01:04:35,204 --> 01:04:40,083
<i>...and, of course, live life abundantly.</i>

686
01:04:52,429 --> 01:04:55,097
Hey. Thanks. Got it.

687
01:04:55,266 --> 01:04:57,099
Hi, Duke.

688
01:04:57,268 --> 01:04:59,351
Hi, baby.

689
01:05:00,353 --> 01:05:02,563
What time does the nurse come?

690
01:05:02,731 --> 01:05:05,608
She should be there by the time I get home.

691
01:05:08,820 --> 01:05:11,155
- Ben?
- Yes.

692
01:05:12,742 --> 01:05:15,744
I know I'm the girl with the broken wing.

693
01:05:16,913 --> 01:05:19,246
But who are you?

694
01:05:19,748 --> 01:05:21,041
Who am I?

695
01:05:21,208 --> 01:05:24,251
I am your friendly neighborhood
tax collector.

696
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:25,920
Ben.

697
01:05:27,380 --> 01:05:29,965
Where the hell did you come from?

698
01:05:32,719 --> 01:05:35,804
I grew up in Oakland.

699
01:05:37,016 --> 01:05:39,266
Literally. Okay.

700
01:05:41,186 --> 01:05:43,438
Where did you go to college?

701
01:05:43,606 --> 01:05:46,858
As far from Oakland as possible.

702
01:05:47,275 --> 01:05:50,320
Massachusetts Institute of Technology.

703
01:05:50,487 --> 01:05:52,280
How about you?

704
01:05:52,447 --> 01:05:54,449
UCLA.

705
01:05:55,701 --> 01:05:58,077
You went to MIT?

706
01:05:58,829 --> 01:06:01,623
Like, the MIT?

707
01:06:04,376 --> 01:06:10,297
Oh, and now you're wondering how
I wound up as a lowly tax collector.

708
01:06:10,465 --> 01:06:12,300
Absolutely.

709
01:06:17,264 --> 01:06:22,268
- I sort of stumbled into this job.
- That's a big stumble.

710
01:06:23,019 --> 01:06:24,728
What from?

711
01:06:26,398 --> 01:06:28,733
I always wanted to be an engineer.

712
01:06:29,652 --> 01:06:31,735
An engineer?

713
01:06:33,572 --> 01:06:35,322
What kind?

714
01:06:36,282 --> 01:06:38,994
The kind that sent people to the moon.

715
01:06:40,329 --> 01:06:41,829
Really?

716
01:06:42,331 --> 01:06:43,414
Yes.

717
01:06:43,581 --> 01:06:46,835
I don't wanna talk about me anymore.

718
01:06:48,086 --> 01:06:52,297
That's too bad, because
you're very interesting.

719
01:07:00,557 --> 01:07:02,266
Have you...?

720
01:07:03,561 --> 01:07:05,603
Have you ever been in love?

721
01:07:06,981 --> 01:07:09,023
Emily, please.

722
01:07:09,733 --> 01:07:11,775
Yes, you have.

723
01:07:11,943 --> 01:07:13,360
Come on, you can tell me.

724
01:07:18,034 --> 01:07:19,784
Yes.

725
01:07:20,119 --> 01:07:22,454
But it ended.

726
01:07:23,371 --> 01:07:26,206
- What happened?
- Stop it.

727
01:07:26,708 --> 01:07:28,876
- No, seriously, you can tell...
- Stop it.

728
01:07:31,213 --> 01:07:33,882
You need to get some rest.

729
01:07:34,592 --> 01:07:38,969
I'll call you tomorrow,
or maybe I'll stop by.

730
01:07:41,766 --> 01:07:45,184
No, if I have questions
tomorrow, what then?

731
01:07:46,978 --> 01:07:49,271
That's not a part of the deal.

732
01:07:50,858 --> 01:07:52,942
What the hell does that mean?

733
01:08:13,630 --> 01:08:16,757
Emily, hold on. Hold on.

734
01:08:16,926 --> 01:08:20,011
- Just leave.
- Emily, wait.

735
01:08:20,179 --> 01:08:21,637
Wait!

736
01:08:32,315 --> 01:08:34,734
Thank you for everything you did.

737
01:09:08,101 --> 01:09:09,769
Did you like the eggs?

738
01:09:09,936 --> 01:09:11,938
They were okay, I guess.

739
01:09:12,105 --> 01:09:14,439
I don't like the eggs you buy.

740
01:09:15,943 --> 01:09:17,609
Okay.

741
01:09:45,514 --> 01:09:47,849
You're wearing suit pants.

742
01:09:48,766 --> 01:09:50,393
To weed.

743
01:09:50,560 --> 01:09:54,689
Yeah, I didn't... I didn't have
any other clothes with me.

744
01:09:55,231 --> 01:09:58,193
- You know, I was gonna get to those.
- I saw them the other day.

745
01:09:58,359 --> 01:10:03,030
I figured I would just take the day off
and get this done for you.

746
01:10:06,034 --> 01:10:07,409
Ben?

747
01:10:07,578 --> 01:10:08,869
Yeah?

748
01:10:09,037 --> 01:10:11,914
This is a really ridiculous apology.

749
01:10:17,837 --> 01:10:21,466
Come on.
I wanna show you something.

750
01:10:21,634 --> 01:10:23,551
Oh, no, I gotta finish.

751
01:10:25,470 --> 01:10:27,555
You can finish tomorrow.

752
01:10:29,057 --> 01:10:30,725
Come on.

753
01:10:45,615 --> 01:10:47,242
This is where I used to work.

754
01:10:48,577 --> 01:10:51,496
And these are the artifacts of said work.

755
01:10:52,081 --> 01:10:54,748
Wow, those are great. How old are they?

