01:10:56,417 --> 01:11:01,797
This one is just shy of 120 years.

757
01:11:02,298 --> 01:11:07,679
It's how I put out my line of letterpress
cards, wedding invitations, invites.

758
01:11:07,845 --> 01:11:09,639
What about this one?

759
01:11:10,140 --> 01:11:12,057
That youngster...

760
01:11:12,225 --> 01:11:17,020
...is the Heidelberg Windmill, 1956.

761
01:11:17,523 --> 01:11:19,439
Call it "The Beast."

762
01:11:20,109 --> 01:11:22,484
Well, that seems appropriate.

763
01:11:22,944 --> 01:11:25,488
It pooped out on me
about five years ago, though.

764
01:11:25,655 --> 01:11:28,283
And I can't find anybody to fix it.

765
01:11:28,449 --> 01:11:30,952
It's kind of a dying art.

766
01:11:31,119 --> 01:11:33,704
Defibrillator here works, though.

767
01:11:33,872 --> 01:11:36,291
Luckily. It kept my business afloat.
Wanna see how?

768
01:11:36,457 --> 01:11:38,167
Please.

769
01:11:38,752 --> 01:11:42,130
Okay. Now, true pressmen...

770
01:11:42,297 --> 01:11:45,675
...hate that we modern girls...

771
01:11:46,301 --> 01:11:48,636
...want a deep impression.

772
01:11:48,804 --> 01:11:53,307
See, for a hundred years, they tried
their damnedest just to kiss it...

773
01:11:53,641 --> 01:11:56,894
...so that it didn't leave an indentation.

774
01:11:57,854 --> 01:12:01,315
Now it's the only way
to prove it's not digital.

775
01:12:06,238 --> 01:12:08,698
I think it feels richer.

776
01:12:11,034 --> 01:12:12,827
You okay?

777
01:12:13,162 --> 01:12:14,953
Yeah.

778
01:12:16,332 --> 01:12:18,373
Look, Ben...

779
01:12:19,792 --> 01:12:25,506
I don't really know anything about you
or where you came from...

780
01:12:26,884 --> 01:12:29,051
...but you keep showing up.

781
01:12:32,264 --> 01:12:34,056
And I'm glad.

782
01:12:35,809 --> 01:12:36,005
Okay.

783
01:12:38,628 --> 01:12:40,229
Okay.

784
01:12:41,273 --> 01:12:44,567
So Duke needs a walk.

785
01:12:44,734 --> 01:12:46,485
Are you interested?

786
01:12:47,154 --> 01:12:48,863
Yes.

787
01:13:00,583 --> 01:13:02,210
Come on.

788
01:13:03,962 --> 01:13:05,880
Hey, hey.

789
01:13:06,881 --> 01:13:08,548
Right here.

790
01:13:08,716 --> 01:13:10,467
There you go.

791
01:13:11,052 --> 01:13:14,055
He's like a different dog with you around.

792
01:13:14,555 --> 01:13:17,391
I don't think we ever properly bonded.

793
01:13:18,810 --> 01:13:21,061
Why would you get such a big dog?

794
01:13:25,274 --> 01:13:31,154
Did you know that Great Danes on
average only live about seven years?

795
01:13:33,242 --> 01:13:35,201
They have heart issues.

796
01:13:37,746 --> 01:13:40,122
I think I got him because...

797
01:13:40,748 --> 01:13:43,333
...I thought he could help me
with my illness.

798
01:13:44,168 --> 01:13:46,128
It'd be something
I could take care of...

799
01:13:46,296 --> 01:13:49,006
...as opposed to being
always taken care of.

800
01:13:53,386 --> 01:13:56,764
You know, just so you know,
I used to be really hot.

801
01:13:58,725 --> 01:14:01,601
Like, unauditably hot.

802
01:14:02,186 --> 01:14:04,146
Is that so?

803
01:14:04,314 --> 01:14:05,856
Yeah.

804
01:14:12,905 --> 01:14:15,949
I haven't felt like this
in a really long time.

805
01:14:25,793 --> 01:14:28,421
There's so many things that I wanna do.

806
01:14:31,632 --> 01:14:33,634
I wanna go on a plane for 13 hours...

807
01:14:33,801 --> 01:14:37,345
...and not have to stress
that I can't reach my doctor.

808
01:14:39,099 --> 01:14:43,810
You know, like, just travel.
Go backpacking, have experiences.

809
01:14:44,604 --> 01:14:46,730
See the world.

810
01:14:48,233 --> 01:14:53,195
I just wanna have the time
to figure out who it is that I am.

811
01:14:53,363 --> 01:14:55,614
You know, what I like.

812
01:14:58,284 --> 01:15:01,496
Do things, try things,
get out of my head for once.

813
01:15:06,001 --> 01:15:09,295
I would really like to go running.

814
01:15:11,131 --> 01:15:12,465
I think about that sometimes.

815
01:15:12,632 --> 01:15:16,927
What it would just feel like
to go running.

816
01:15:51,755 --> 01:15:53,506
So...

817
01:15:54,550 --> 01:15:56,091
...see you tomorrow?

818
01:15:57,552 --> 01:15:59,136
Yes.

819
01:16:00,264 --> 01:16:05,225
But if you need anything,
just call and I'll come right back.

820
01:16:06,395 --> 01:16:07,979
Okay.

821
01:16:15,237 --> 01:16:16,737
Bye.

822
01:16:28,207 --> 01:16:30,083
I had a really great time today.

823
01:16:30,586 --> 01:16:32,377
Me too.

824
01:16:33,796 --> 01:16:35,463
Bye.

825
01:20:45,756 --> 01:20:48,801
No anesthetic. You ever
donated bone marrow before?

826
01:20:48,969 --> 01:20:50,845
You're a brave guy.

827
01:20:53,597 --> 01:20:55,975
How long have you known Nicholas?

828
01:21:05,734 --> 01:21:07,778
What the hell happened to you?

829
01:21:09,738 --> 01:21:12,783
Hey, how much longer are you
gonna stay in my hotel?

830
01:21:12,951 --> 01:21:14,201
Motel.

831
01:21:14,368 --> 01:21:16,244
How much longer?

832
01:21:17,204 --> 01:21:20,207
Actually, I was planning
on dying here.

833
01:21:20,625 --> 01:21:23,335
Well, then you need to pay
in advance.

834
01:22:15,220 --> 01:22:16,305
Hello?

835
01:22:18,350 --> 01:22:19,934
Hey, it's Emily.

836
01:22:20,100 --> 01:22:21,685
Are you sleeping?

837
01:22:24,104 --> 01:22:26,689
Yes. No.

838
01:22:27,900 --> 01:22:29,359
Is everything okay?

839
01:22:30,444 --> 01:22:32,488
Yeah, I'm fine.

840
01:22:33,698 --> 01:22:36,783
My sister came over for a couple
of days last week with the kids...

841
01:22:36,952 --> 01:22:39,453
...and it was really great.

842
01:22:40,747 --> 01:22:43,498
<i>I tried calling you a couple times.</i>

843
01:22:43,667 --> 01:22:45,250
<i>How are you doing?</i>

844
01:22:45,417 --> 01:22:47,252
Yeah, I'm good.

845
01:22:47,420 --> 01:22:50,421
Everything's fine. I've been...

846
01:22:50,966 --> 01:22:54,801
I've been traveling a lot, so...

847
01:22:57,764 --> 01:22:59,722
Well, are you busy tonight?

848
01:23:01,475 --> 01:23:02,810
