887
01:27:34,164 --> 01:27:36,250
It's delicious.

888
01:27:38,795 --> 01:27:40,628
Glad you like it.

889
01:28:20,877 --> 01:28:23,130
Do you wanna hear my favorite song?

890
01:28:24,172 --> 01:28:26,550
Yes. Are you gonna sing it?

891
01:28:30,846 --> 01:28:32,972
No, I can't sing anymore.

892
01:28:33,932 --> 01:28:35,641
Oh, and a performance.

893
01:28:35,810 --> 01:28:37,685
Oh, no.

894
01:29:21,189 --> 01:29:22,939
Shall we?

895
01:29:42,167 --> 01:29:43,877
You need to relax.

896
01:29:44,878 --> 01:29:47,088
This is relaxed.

897
01:30:18,912 --> 01:30:21,331
I have a surprise for you.

898
01:30:23,417 --> 01:30:25,252
Surprise?

899
01:30:26,002 --> 01:30:27,587
Yes.

900
01:30:28,296 --> 01:30:29,797
For me?

901
01:30:33,010 --> 01:30:35,429
- Keep them closed.
- Okay.

902
01:30:42,310 --> 01:30:45,104
And open.

903
01:30:49,819 --> 01:30:51,278
Okay.

904
01:30:58,828 --> 01:31:00,912
You cleaned The Beast.

905
01:31:02,164 --> 01:31:04,623
Actually, I fixed it.

906
01:31:05,501 --> 01:31:07,293
No, you didn't.

907
01:31:07,462 --> 01:31:09,212
Oh, okay, let's go, then.

908
01:31:09,380 --> 01:31:12,381
Wait. Are you serious?

909
01:31:12,550 --> 01:31:14,134
Try it.

910
01:31:22,601 --> 01:31:24,185
Okay.

911
01:32:07,854 --> 01:32:09,564
Thank you.

912
01:32:49,814 --> 01:32:52,774
Wait right here, okay?

913
01:32:53,109 --> 01:32:55,652
I'll be right back. Wait right here.

914
01:32:58,823 --> 01:33:00,239
One second.

915
01:33:12,127 --> 01:33:13,587
Hey!

916
01:33:14,671 --> 01:33:16,506
Tell me what's going on.

917
01:33:17,007 --> 01:33:18,341
- Now!
- All right.

918
01:33:18,509 --> 01:33:20,676
Ben, you need to go home.

919
01:33:20,845 --> 01:33:24,805
Do you know they keep a full history of
every inquiry a revenue officer makes?

920
01:33:24,974 --> 01:33:26,765
- You understand?
- Keep your voice down.

921
01:33:26,934 --> 01:33:30,103
- Just keep your voice down.
- No. What you are doing is a crime!

922
01:33:30,270 --> 01:33:32,771
You are impersonating
a federal officer. It's a felony!

923
01:33:32,939 --> 01:33:34,189
All right. Listen.

924
01:33:34,358 --> 01:33:37,819
You can't play with people's lives.
Do you understand that?

925
01:33:37,987 --> 01:33:41,197
All right. All right,
there's a coffee shop.

926
01:33:41,364 --> 01:33:43,449
There's a coffee shop
near where I'm staying.

927
01:33:43,618 --> 01:33:46,202
- Tomorrow we'll sit down...
- Where are you staying, Tim?

928
01:33:46,369 --> 01:33:48,954
Tell me, because I don't know
where my brother lives!

929
01:33:50,166 --> 01:33:51,791
A motel. Five blocks from here.

930
01:33:51,958 --> 01:33:54,293
We'll sit down tomorrow morning,
I guarantee it.

931
01:33:54,462 --> 01:33:57,212
Where are my credentials?
Give me my credentials back.

932
01:34:03,845 --> 01:34:06,389
Here it is. Here. Here.

933
01:34:08,141 --> 01:34:09,684
Just go home.

934
01:34:09,851 --> 01:34:13,020
You have a beautiful family.
Go home and enjoy them.

935
01:34:13,189 --> 01:34:15,481
Tim, Tim, Tim, why are you even here?

936
01:34:15,649 --> 01:34:18,318
Tell me, who is Emily Posa?

937
01:34:21,029 --> 01:34:23,113
I'll explain everything tomorrow.

938
01:34:28,703 --> 01:34:30,829
Look, give me your car keys.

939
01:34:38,005 --> 01:34:40,131
I'm not going anywhere.

940
01:34:40,841 --> 01:34:42,841
I'm gonna be right here.

941
01:34:44,220 --> 01:34:48,264
So you remember I love you and...

942
01:34:49,850 --> 01:34:52,101
Tim, don't make me come knock
on the door, okay?

943
01:35:18,921 --> 01:35:23,173
I didn't realize how late it was and...

944
01:35:25,886 --> 01:35:29,805
I have a really long drive,
so I need to go.

945
01:35:33,476 --> 01:35:35,478
I don't wanna keep lying to you.

946
01:35:36,689 --> 01:35:39,899
I don't wanna... Wait, Emily.

947
01:37:40,311 --> 01:37:42,521
Do you wanna play a game?

948
01:37:44,190 --> 01:37:45,859
What game?

949
01:37:48,863 --> 01:37:55,033
The "what if" game.

950
01:37:56,494 --> 01:37:58,371
What if...

951
01:37:59,873 --> 01:38:02,041
...my pager goes off...

952
01:38:04,962 --> 01:38:07,046
...and it's a heart...

953
01:38:08,131 --> 01:38:10,132
...and...

954
01:38:11,051 --> 01:38:12,886
...it works?

955
01:38:14,470 --> 01:38:17,222
And my body doesn't reject it?

956
01:38:19,475 --> 01:38:21,394
And...

957
01:38:25,858 --> 01:38:28,192
...what if I have time?

958
01:38:41,623 --> 01:38:43,457
What if...?

959
01:38:48,463 --> 01:38:51,048
What if we have children?

960
01:38:56,555 --> 01:38:58,931
What if we got married?

961
01:39:12,820 --> 01:39:14,529
I love you.

962
01:39:14,698 --> 01:39:17,115
- I love you too.
- I love you.

963
01:41:12,858 --> 01:41:14,442
Hi.

964
01:41:14,902 --> 01:41:17,779
Is Dr. Briar on duty tonight?

965
01:41:18,572 --> 01:41:20,113
She's doing her rounds.

966
01:41:20,282 --> 01:41:23,076
Can you tell her it's Ben Thomas?

967
01:41:23,743 --> 01:41:24,786
It's very important.

968
01:41:25,328 --> 01:41:28,247
- I'll... I'll page her.
- Thank you.

969
01:41:30,333 --> 01:41:33,293
Dr. Briar to the nurses' station.

970
01:41:58,862 --> 01:42:00,404
Hey.

971
01:42:01,280 --> 01:42:04,449
- Is it Emily?
- No, no.

972
01:42:05,953 --> 01:42:07,662
I'm sorry.

973
01:42:09,539 --> 01:42:10,957
It's...

974
01:42:11,291 --> 01:42:13,042
Is there...?

975
01:42:15,295 --> 01:42:16,837
I'm sorry.

976
01:42:17,338 --> 01:42:21,591
Do you have any more optimism...

977
01:42:21,760 --> 01:42:24,345
...about Emily...

978
01:42:24,971 --> 01:42:27,305
...than you did the other day?

979
01:42:27,975 --> 01:42:29,391
Ben...

980
01:42:30,394 --> 01:42:35,398
...when you're looking for a donor
with a rare blood type...

981
01:42:36,733 --> 01:42:38,359
...the odds go way down.

982
01:42:38,985 --> 01:42:40,485
To what?

983
01:42:41,404 --> 01:42:43,488
They go down. What's the...?

984
01:42:43,657 --> 01:42:45,699
Give me a percentage.

985
01:42:46,952 --> 01:42:48,661
Give me a number.

986
01:42:49,662 --> 01:42:51,913
Three, 5 percent.

987
01:42:53,000 --> 01:42:55,542
I know. I'm sorry.
I wish the numbers were higher.

988
01:42:55,711 --> 01:42:58,171
- Thank you. Thank you.
- I do.

989
01:43:44,176 --> 01:43:45,384
Hello?

990
01:43:46,052 --> 01:43:47,595
Dan.

991
01:43:48,512 --> 01:43:50,222
It's time.

992
01:43:50,890 --> 01:43:52,515
I love you.

993
01:44:49,198 --> 01:44:51,993
<i>1:38 a.m.</i>

994
01:44:55,037 --> 01:44:56,288
Hello?

995
01:44:56,456 --> 01:44:58,332
Ezra.

996
01:45:00,752 --> 01:45:03,087
My name is Ben Thomas.

997
01:45:04,797 --> 01:45:07,800
I called you a few weeks ago.
You probably don't remember.

998
01:45:09,219 --> 01:45:12,179
I do remember.

999
01:45:12,346 --> 01:45:15,349
<i>I wanna apologize for
being so cruel to you...</i>

1000
01:45:15,850 --> 01:45:17,935
...but I had to be certain.

1001
01:45:18,895 --> 01:45:22,355
I had to be certain that you
were a decent man. Kind.

1002
01:45:22,524 --> 01:45:26,068
- <i>Slow to anger.</i>
- What do you want from me?

1003
01:45:27,029 --> 01:45:29,279
I wanna give you a gift.

1004
01:45:30,323 --> 01:45:34,076
You're gonna be contacted
by a man named Dan Morris.

1005
01:45:35,078 --> 01:45:37,203
<i>You can trust him.</i>

1006
01:45:37,372 --> 01:45:39,707
Was that you at the diner?

1007
01:45:41,585 --> 01:45:42,752
Goodbye.

1008
01:46:05,233 --> 01:46:07,359
<i>911 emergency.</i>

1009
01:46:11,782 --> 01:46:13,573
I need an ambulance.

1010
01:46:13,742 --> 01:46:18,371
<i>I have you at 9212 West Third Street
in Los Angeles.</i>

1011
01:46:21,541 --> 01:46:23,542
Yes, room number 2.

1012
01:46:24,252 --> 01:46:26,420
<i>What's the emergency?</i>

1013
01:46:28,840 --> 01:46:31,050
There's been a suicide.

1014
01:46:31,217 --> 01:46:33,051
<i>Who's the victim?</i>

1015
01:46:35,012 --> 01:46:36,389
I am.

1016
01:46:38,307 --> 01:46:41,018
You are gonna need to stop
looking at that thing so much.

1017
01:46:41,185 --> 01:46:43,895
Why? Is it gonna crack?

1018
01:46:44,064 --> 01:46:46,689
Oh, no. I paid extra
for the non-cracking kind.

1019
01:46:46,858 --> 01:46:48,567
I bet you did.

1020
01:46:49,319 --> 01:46:52,404
- Why don't you just turn that off?
- I know. No more. No more work.

1021
01:46:52,572 --> 01:46:54,239
I'm done. Almost done. Almost done.

1022
01:46:54,408 --> 01:46:55,949
